##As an ordinary patient, how to seek medical treatment in time during the epidemic?

WMSYGSDR

Functional introduction, each line has a serious person, even ordinary people have extraordinary stories. Huazhong University of Science and Technology Press Official non-fiction story platform, the story of the people will meet here.

1

February 4th was the outbreak.

Hospitals are crowded with feverish outpatients, and hospital wards are still hard to find. I obey the arrangement of the hospital, was transferred to the hospital emergency transfer center to work, began to contact the epidemic forgotten a category of serious patients.

At that time, Wuhan had already enlisted hotels and party schools in various neighborhoods to quarantine all suspected patients, a shelter hospital has been set up at the Hankou International Convention and Exhibition Centre, the Wuhan Living Room and the Wembley Arena in Wuchang to concentrate the isolation of confirmed cases. Among them, critically ill patients will be arranged according to the staff, sent to the hospital for systematic treatment.

On February 9, Wuhan will begin intensive care with pre-hospital confirmed cases of severe pneumonia, which will also be admitted to our emergency transfer center.

That day, we received a 120 dispatch center of the car, the ambulance will be sterilized and then drive to the destination.

Upon arrival, we found that the scene is a 70-year-old father, due to the unfortunate infection of coronavirus, respiratory difficulties, Oxygenation drop, need to continue to be hospitalized symptomatic treatment.

However, the infected must be reported through the community trans-shipment. Previously, the family has repeatedly contacted the community staff, there is a repeated response is: "has been registered, waiting for row beds. "

The family immediately anxious, the emotion excitedly stressed that the patient condition has been very serious, the urgent need to be hospitalized.

Later, the community was able to arrange to go to Tongji Hospital. So, we loaded the patient into the car, and off we went. It was dark, and the road was cold and empty on winter nights because of the epidemic

Arriving at the hospital gate, we were intercepted by the staff, had to explain: "We are the community referral contact to the hospital, the patient is now in an urgent situation, please pass under. "

The clerk looked up at us. "Get in line behind the bus. "

Then we noticed that there were several buses parked in front of the house, all carrying patients from the shelter hospital, waiting for beds as well. We have no choice. The patient is too old to move. We have to wait with the patient. Later, in the cold wind waiting for more than two hours, the front of the team is not loose, the patient in the unbearable circumstances had to choose to go home.

2

Wuhan is now the epicentre of the outbreak, and new Crown Infections are a national concern. But beyond the epidemic, there is a special group of people who also need attention. For example those suffering from chronic diseases need long-term medication, cancer radiotherapy and chemotherapy and uremia patients.

One day, on the day shift, just after 8:00 in the morning, I got my bus schedule. The message was coma patient, but when I got there, I was still shocked.

I saw a toilet door on the ground prone more than 70 mother-in-law, face down, motionless. We used to roll patients over on their backs, their lips were purple, they were foaming at the mouth, and when we checked, we found that there were no signs of life.

There is only one wife at home, according to Daddy, said mother-in-law usually good, just these two days in addition to a sore throat other than what is not comfortable, today she went to the toilet suddenly heard a muffled ring, so quickly come over, found that has not answered.

"You did not come over, I dare not move. " Father in the side added. I noticed that the jade bracelet on my mother-in-law's wrist might have broken when I fell, and I had a bad feeling about it. Then, inform the mother-in-law may have been gone for a period of time, condolences.

Father trembled to contact the children, until we later left, his mouth is still repeating: "clearly yesterday or well, how suddenly gone, how... " only left a lonely figure and heavy sigh.

When ordinary people have an emergency, the first thing they think of is 120. But in the process, from the 120 dispatch center to arrange a car, put on the isolation suit, to the whole car disinfection, the process will take more than 10 minutes, may be the golden age of saving patients. And even if the patient to the hospital, but also through fever clinics screening, after a series of procedures to be treated.

We can not afford to be ill in the face of this severe epidemic!

When I got back, before I could sit down to rest, I received a request from the 120 dispatch center that a comatose mother-in-law needed emergency treatment. So, after sterilizing the ambulance, we set off.

Arriving, it was a 60-year-old mother-in-law lying in bed, which was inappropriate. We checked the patient's vital signs and asked if he had a history of fever and cough.

One side of the son said: "The old man this time has no fever, is diabetes, usually not good blood sugar control, this time the community closed tight, the old man also dare not go to the hospital to check, at home their own medication in. "

"The old man used to go to the hospital regularly for check-up and monitoring. I didn't hear her say anything was wrong these days. I didn't expect to wake her up suddenly. Is My mother all right? " The son's voice was a little impatient and worried, adding.

We immediately took the patient to ECG monitoring, check blood sugar low, so the elderly to establish an intravenous channel, injection of Glucose, still no remission, immediately ready to send to the hospital for systematic treatment. The driver asks the patient to prepare a camp bed and take precautions. It may be necessary to wait.

Sure enough, to the Concorde Emergency Room, found full inside, patients can only in the outpatient registration line, we and those doctors to do a good hand-over, then left.

3

Later, according to the order of the provincial command for the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia, only the Wuhan Tongji Hospital, the Wuhan Union Hospital Hospital and the headquarters of the Hubei Provincial People's Hospital were allowed to receive non-new crown pneumonia patients in Wuhan, every other hospital in Wuhan has been commandeered as a new crown pneumonia site-specific hospital.

In the critical period of the epidemic, communities in Wuhan have implemented more stringent personnel control policies, except for community workers, volunteers, medical personnel, and other people can travel, strict restrictions on access.

During this period, the average emergency patient wants to see a doctor, must through community certification, contact the three designated hospitals to receive patients. These days, as the community has stepped up the screening of fever patients, arranged for a car escort isolation, so we are more responsible for the non-infected emergency transit.

That night, we received the 120 dispatch center's instructions to go to the construction road to pick up a coma patient.

Later arrived at the destination, the accident is a 70-year-old mother-in-law, according to the family, the patient in the day before the coma will complain of unilateral upper and lower limb weakness, hypertension and other basic diseases. The patient was in a shallow coma and was initially considered to have suffered a stroke.

So, as we escorted the patient to the stretcher, we asked the family if they would contact the community staff to arrange medical transport. We also explained to the family that currently, non-infected patients must also go through the community to arrange medical dispatch, there's no guarantee of a bed until 120 arrives.

The family said the community had responded and was willing to send a staff member, so we put the patient in the car. But when they left, the community workers said they were "too busy" to go with them, and the family became impatient and called 110 for help in the face of the elderly's precarious situation.

The 110 responded to the call, calmed the family and began mediation, persuading the driver to escort the patient to the designated hospital while urging the community to arrange personnel.

Our driver also expressed his frustration, "we have run several times, Tongji Association and the Emergency Room are full, are in need of urgent treatment of patients, no community transfer order, there is no emergency treatment. "

"But the community there is not said to have been arranged, can pass. " The family in the side road.

"It's usually safer to go with someone, " the driver insisted. The two sides could not hold out for a while, and the atmosphere was tense.

After all, the longer we wait outside, the more danger we may be in. At this time the family also tried to call the mayor hotline, Busy Line, can not solve the problem.

At last, the family tried to smooth things over, and the driver finally set off.

At the Concorde Emergency Room, there were a large number of patients, some even brought their own cots waiting for the doctor in the room. We finally got the chance to explain the situation to the doctor, but the doctor could only say that he had to wait in line.

The emergency room is supposed to be filled with sudden pain or emergency situations, and the doctor races against the clock every day, physically and mentally. After the outbreak of the new crown disease, the emergency department is not only the front line of first-aid treatment for trauma patients in hospitals, but also the first line of the fight against the disease. It not only undertakes the task of treating emergency patients in Wuhan, but also needs to do a good job of screening for COVID-19 pneumonia,
Patients are usually escorted to the operating room to complete a chest CT scan and rule out new pneumonia.

While this greatly delays patient visits, if the emergency patient is not properly screened, there is a risk of infecting more innocent doctors or patients.

This reality, let a person helpless and sad.

In the enclosed area, there are most of the patients with chronic diseases, or through online consultation, post for help, or someone else to buy the status quo barely. If it had not been for this outbreak, many of them would have been reexamined or treated in time. All we can do is get the patient to the hospital as safely as possible.

In this COVID-19, everyone who is sick is struggling, fighting in their own way.

I hope this storm can treat everyone well!

-END-

By sugi Sugi, young author.
